        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 12:24AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1224 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
I-10 Near The Crockett-Pecos County Line, or over Sheffield, moving
north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ft Lancaster, I-10 Near The Crockett-Pecos County Line, and The
Intersection Of I-10 And Highway 290.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 327 and 343.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
